{"lemma":"سَدِّ","slug":"سَدِّ","root":"س.د.د","root_slug":"س-د-د","root_link":"/words/roots/س-د-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"سَدّ","root":"سدد","pos":"N","occurrence_count":4},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":11},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n19280","","n19282","n19283","n19284","n19396"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8E%D8%AF%D9%90%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to close up, to seal off"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to obstruct, to block, to bar"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to repair"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to fill (a gap)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to grant compensation; to redeem (a debt)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be truthful"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to hit on the right thing, be to the point"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of سَدَّ (sadda) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of سَدَّ (sadda) (form I); sealing, shutting off, obstruction, closure, shutdown"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"dam, dike"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"barrier, obstacle, hurdle, bar"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n19280","headword_ar":"سَدَّ","root":"sd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, A, Mgh, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sad~N","text_ar":"سَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, M, Mgh, Msb;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sd~d","text_ar":"سدّد","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M;) [but the latter has an intensive signification, or relates to several objects;]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He closed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"closed up,"},{"kind":"text","text":"an interstice, or intervening space: (M:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stopped,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stopped up,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"repaired, and made firm"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strong,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K,) a breach, or gap, (S, M, A, Mgh, Msb, K,) and the like. (S, Msb.) ―         -b2-  [Hence one says,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sud~ato Ealayohi","text_ar":"سُدَّتْ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlT~ariyqu","text_ar":"الطَّرِيقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The road,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"way, became closed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stopped, against him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sud~a Tariyquhu mino","text_ar":"سُدَّ طَرِيقُهُ مِنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayoni yadayohi wamano xalofihi","text_ar":"بَيْنِ يَدَيْهِ وَمَنْ خَلْفِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His road,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"way, became closed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stopped, before him and behind him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Zj, M.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sad~a AlA^ufuqa","text_ar":"سَدَّ الاُفُقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It obstructed the horizon"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; said of a multitudinous swarm of locusts. (S, A, * K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sad~a Ealayohimo","text_ar":"سَدَّ عَلَيْهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asad~a","text_ar":"اَسَدَّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It closed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obstructed, against them, the horizon;"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^ufuqa","text_ar":"الاُفُقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being understood;] said of a collection of clouds rising. (M.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sad~a maA waraA='ahu","text_ar":"سَدَّ مَا وَرَا=ءَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It barred,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"excluded, what was behind it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M.) ―         -b3-  [Hence also,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sadadotu Ealayohi baAba AlkalaAmi","text_ar":"سَدَدْتُ عَلَيْهِ بَابَ الكَلَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I closed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stopped, to him the door of speech;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I prevented him from speaking;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as though I closed, or stopped, his mouth. (Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA sadadotu","text_ar":"مَا سَدَدْتُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY lahawaAti xaSomK qaT~u","text_ar":"عَلَى لَهَوَاتِ خَصْمٍ قَطُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I never stopped the way of speech of an adversary, nor prevented his saying what was in his mind."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Shureyh, Mgh.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA sadadotu EalaY xaSomK qaT~u","text_ar":"مَا سَدَدْتُ عَلَى خَصْمٍ قَطُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I never stopped an adversary from speaking;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(El-Fáïk, Mgh, L;) on the authority of Esh-Shaabee: (Mgh:) occurring in a trad. (L.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abiyhi","text_ar":"اَبِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa yasud~u masad~a","text_ar":"هُوَ يَسُدُّ مَسَدَّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He fills up,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"supplies, the place of his father"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asolaAfihimo","text_ar":"اَسْلَافِهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yasud~uwna masad~a","text_ar":"يَسُدُّونَ مَسَدَّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They fill up,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"supply, the place of their ancestors"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yusad~u bihi AlHaAjapu","text_ar":"يُسَدُّ بِهِ الحَاجَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Want is supplied thereby:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, * TA:) [whence the saying,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taSad~aquwA walawo","text_ar":"تَصَدَّقُوا وَلَوْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bitamorapK faA_in~ahaA tasud~u mina AljaAy^iEi","text_ar":"بِتَمْرَةٍ فَاـِنَّهَا تَسُدُّ مِنَ الجَايِعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Give ye something as alms, though it be but a date,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a dried date; for it will supply somewhat of the want of the hungry"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: a trad. (El-Jámi' es-Sagheer.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yasud~u Alr~amaqa","text_ar":"يَسُدُّ الرَّمَقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It stays,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"arrests, the remains of life;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as though it stopped the passage of the last breath from the body; or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it maintains, and preserves, the strength."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rmq","text_ar":"رمق"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sad~ahu","text_ar":"سَدَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He attributed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"imputed, to him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he charged him with,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"accused him of, a fault;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as though he thereby stopped his mouth; (see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sad~N","text_ar":"سَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":";)] as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sat~ahu","text_ar":"سَتَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"st","text_ar":"ست"},{"kind":"text","text":".)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sad~a","text_ar":"سَدَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yasid~u","text_ar":"يَسِدُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, L, K,) with kesr, (S,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sadaAdN","text_ar":"سَدَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suduwdN","text_ar":"سُدُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L, the former inf. n. expl. in the S and K as signifying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AisotiqaAmapN","text_ar":"اِسْتِقَامَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",) said of a spear, and an arrow, (TA,) and a saying, (S,) and an action, (TA,) or a thing [absolutely]; (L;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sad~a","text_ar":"سَدَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [sec. pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sadidota","text_ar":"سَدِدْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yasad~u","text_ar":"يَسَدُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with fet-h to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"s","text_ar":"س"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sadadN","text_ar":"سَدَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TK, expl. in the S and K as signifying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AisotiqaAmapN","text_ar":"اِسْتِقَامَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sadaAdN","text_ar":"سَدَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", of which it is said in the S to be a contraction,) said of a saying, and an affair; (A;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sad~a","text_ar":"سَدَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yasid~u","text_ar":"يَسِدُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yasad~u","text_ar":"يَسَدُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sadadN","text_ar":"سَدَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (MA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAra sadiydFA","text_ar":"صَارَ سَدِيدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, right, direct,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a right state; it had,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"took, a right direction"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tendency; it tended towards the right point"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"object"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, A, L, K, TA:) and [in like manner] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Astd~","text_ar":"استدّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AisotaqaAma","text_ar":"اِسْتَقَامَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which signifies the same]; (S, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Asd~","text_ar":"اسدّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tsd~d","text_ar":"تسدّد","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Astd~","text_ar":"استدّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of an affair signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, rightly ordered"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disposed; in a right state."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahu","text_ar":"لَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tsd~d","text_ar":"تسدّد","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Astd~","text_ar":"استدّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, rightly directed towards it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAEiduhu","text_ar":"سَاعِدُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Astd~","text_ar":"استدّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tsd~d","text_ar":"تسدّد","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His fore arm was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, in a right state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rightly directed,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY Alr~amoYi","text_ar":"عَلَى الرَّمْىِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for shooting"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AstqAm","text_ar":"استقام"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A.) A poet says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"saAEiduhu ramaAniY ↓ \n      falam~aA A@sotad~a \n                      \n                     \n                        A^uEal~imuhu Alr~imaAyapa kul~a yawomK"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I teaching him the art of shooting every day; and when his fore arm became in a right state, he shot me"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: As says that [the reading]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A$td~","text_ar":"اشتدّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$","text_ar":"ش"},{"kind":"text","text":", is not to be regarded. (S, TA.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sad~a","text_ar":"سَدَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yasid~u","text_ar":"يَسِدُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"s","text_ar":"س"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, Msb, TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suduwdN","text_ar":"سُدُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb) [and app. also, as above,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sadaAdN","text_ar":"سَدَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v. infrà], is said of a man, (A, Msb, TA,) in like manner meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAra sadiydFA","text_ar":"صَارَ سَدِيدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, in a right state; he had,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"took, a right direction"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tendency; he tended towards the right point"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"object"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (A, TA:) or, (Msb,) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Asd~","text_ar":"اسدّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he hit the right thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K, TA,) in his saying (S, Msb, TA) and in his action: (Msb:) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Asd~","text_ar":"اسدّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he said,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"did, what was right:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he sought what was right;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sd~d","text_ar":"سدّد","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (L;) or it has this last meaning also. (S, * L.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY Alqawoli","text_ar":"فِى القَوْلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu layusid~u","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَيُسِدُّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he hits the right thing in the saying."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qado","text_ar":"قَدْ"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1329},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA $iy^ota","text_ar":"مَا شِيْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asodadota","text_ar":"اَسْدَدْتَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * L) is said to a man when he seeks [or has sought] what is right, (S,) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou hast sought what is right;"},{"kind":"text","text":"whether the person thus addressed have hit the right thing or not. (L.) One says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sad~a Ealayoka Alr~ajulu","text_ar":"سَدَّ عَلَيْكَ الرَّجُلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yasid~u","text_ar":"يَسِدُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sd","text_ar":"سد"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sadaAd","text_ar":"سَدَاد"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suduwd","text_ar":"سُدُود"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The man said,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"did, what was right"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"against thee"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: so in the handwriting of Sh. (Az, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","A","Mgh","Msb","K","L","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n19282","headword_ar":"سَدٌّ","root":"sd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sud~N","text_ar":"سُدٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Any building,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"construction, with which a place is closed"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"closed up,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stopped"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stopped up:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M: [see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sidaAdN","text_ar":"سِدَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a dam:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing intervening, as a separation, a partition, a fence, a barrier, a rampart,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an obstacle,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obstruction, between two other things;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a mountain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K: [in the last it seems that this meaning is restricted to the former word; but if restricted to either, it should be to the latter:]) or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anything that faces one,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is over against one, and bars,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"excludes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yasud~u","text_ar":"يَسُدُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is behind it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"whence goats are said to be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sad~N yuraY mino waraAy^ihi Alfaqoru","text_ar":"سَدٌّ يُرَى مِنْ وَرَايِهِ الفَقْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a barrier behind which is seen poverty"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; meaning that they are not of great utility: (M:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sad~N","text_ar":"سَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is made by man;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sud~N","text_ar":"سُدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is created by God,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj, M, Msb, K,) as"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a mountain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) in the Kur xviii. 92 and 93, and xxxvi. 8, some read with fet-h, and some with damm: (M, TA:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asodaAdN","text_ar":"اَسْدَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [a pl. of pauc.,] (A, Msb,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asid~apN","text_ar":"اَسِدَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [also a pl. of pauc.,] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suduwdN","text_ar":"سُدُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [a pl. of mult.,] the latter of these two agreeable with general analogy, and the former of them anomalous, or, [ISd says,] in my opinion, this ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asid~apN","text_ar":"اَسِدَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":") is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sidaAdN","text_ar":"سِدَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Duriba bayonahumaA sad~N","text_ar":"ضُرِبَ بَيْنَهُمَا سَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sud~N","text_ar":"سُدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A barrier,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an obstacle, was set between them two"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Duribato bayonahumaA AlA^asodaAdu","text_ar":"ضُرِبَتْ بَيْنَهُمَا الاَسْدَادُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Barriers,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obstacles, were set between them two"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Darabato Ealayohi AlA^aroDu biAlA^asodaAdi","text_ar":"ضَرَبَتْ عَلَيْهِ الاَرْضُ بِالاَسْدَادِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The earth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"land, set barriers,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obstacles, against him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the ways became closed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stopped, against him, and the courses that he should pursue became obscure to him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K: in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Duribato","text_ar":"ضُرِبَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":":) the sing. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asodaAdN","text_ar":"اَسْدَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[accord. to general analogy] is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sud~N","text_ar":"سُدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,] the former ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sad~N","text_ar":"سَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":") also signifies, (Fr, S, M, L, K,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sidaAdN","text_ar":"سِدَادٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A,) or the former and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sadaAdapN","text_ar":"سَدَادَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A fault,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"defect,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, S, M, A, &c.,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as blindness"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deafness"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dumbness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as closes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stops, one's mouth, so that he does not speak:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) pl. of the first, (S, M, K,) or of the second, (A,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asid~apN","text_ar":"اَسِدَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [a pl. of pauc.,] (S, M, A, K,) accord. to analogy"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suduwdN","text_ar":"سُدُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asud~N","text_ar":"اَسُدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is a pl. of pauc.]. (M.) You say, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA bihi sidaAdN","text_ar":"مَا بِهِ سِدَادٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There is not in him any fault"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN bariYo'N mina","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ بَرِىْءٌ مِنَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^asid~api","text_ar":"الاَسِدَّةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is free from faults"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. (A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tasud~u faAhu Eani AlkalaAmi","text_ar":"تَسُدُّ فَاهُ عَنِ الكَلَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA bifulaAnK sadaAdapN","text_ar":"مَا بِفُلَانٍ سَدَادَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There is not in such a one a fault that stops his mouth from speaking."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Aboo-Sa'eed, L.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA tajoEalan~a","text_ar":"لَا تَجْعَلَنَّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bijanobika AlA^asid~apa","text_ar":"بِجَنْبِكَ الاَسِدَّةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"By no means render thou thy bosom contracted so that thou shalt be unable to return an answer, like him who is deaf or dumb."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) ―         -b3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sud~N","text_ar":"سُدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sd~","text_ar":"سدّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[so in the TA, i. e. either"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sad~N","text_ar":"سَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sud~a","text_ar":"سُدَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] also signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A she-camel by which the sportsman conceals himself from the game;"},{"kind":"text","text":"also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dariyoy^apNnd","text_ar":"دَرِيْيَةٌند"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dariyEapN","text_ar":"دَرِيعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"whence the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramaAhu fiY sd~i naAqatihi","text_ar":"رَمَاهُ فِى سدِّ نَاقَتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He shot him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shot at him, by his she-camel whereby he was concealing himself"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (IAar, TA.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sad~N","text_ar":"سَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sud~N","text_ar":"سُدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K,) is also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zil~N","text_ar":"ظِلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Shade,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shadow;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cover,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"protection"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (IAar, M, O, K, TA.) A poet cited by IAar says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"qaEadotu lahu fiY sad~i niqoDK muEaw~adK\n                      \n                     \n                        li*`lika fiY SaHoraA='a ji*omK dariynuhaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I sat for him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lay in wait for him, in the shade,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cover, of a camel rendered lean by travel, accustomed to that, in a desert whereof the dry herbage was old"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: i. e. I made him a cover, or screen, to me, in order that he might not see me: and by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ji*om","text_ar":"جِذْم"},{"kind":"text","text":"he means “ old, ” because"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alji*omu","text_ar":"الجِذْمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aSolu","text_ar":"الاَصْلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and there is nothing older than the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSol","text_ar":"اَصْل"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and he uses it as an epithet because it implies the meaning of an epithet. (M.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sad~N","text_ar":"سَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,) [i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"basket such as is called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sal~ap","text_ar":"سَلَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made of twigs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and having covers"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aTobaAq","text_ar":"اَطْبَاق"},{"kind":"text","text":"): (S, K: [but this addition in the S and K seems properly to apply to the pl., as will be shown by what  follows:]) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sidaAdN","text_ar":"سِدَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suduwdN","text_ar":"سُدُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, TA:) or, accord. to Lth,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suduwdN","text_ar":"سُدُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"baskets such as are called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"silaAl","text_ar":"سِلَال"},{"kind":"text","text":", [pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sal~apN","text_ar":"سَلَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made of twigs, and having covers"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aTobaAq","text_ar":"اَطْبَاق"},{"kind":"text","text":");"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one of which is called"},{"kind":"text","text":"[not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sad~N","text_ar":"سَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"but] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sad~apN","text_ar":"سَدَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": and it is said also on other authority that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sal~ap","text_ar":"سَلَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sad~apN","text_ar":"سَدَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TabolN","text_ar":"طَبْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","S","K","M","Zj","TA","A","Fr","L","O"]},{"entry_id":"n19283","headword_ar":"سُدٌّ","root":"sd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the next preceding paragraph, passim. ―         -b2-  Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A swarm of locusts obstructing the horizon:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sud~N mino jaraAdK","text_ar":"سُدٌّ مِنْ جَرَادٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaraAdN","text_ar":"جَرَادٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sud~N","text_ar":"سُدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"locusts"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, A, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that have obstructed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obstructing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, A,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the horizon,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, A, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by their multitude:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K:) in which case,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sud~N","text_ar":"سُدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is either a substitute for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaraAdN","text_ar":"جَرَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and therefore a substantive, or it is pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saduwdN","text_ar":"سَدُودٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying that"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which obstructs the horizon"},{"kind":"text","text":"and therefore an epithet. (M.) ―         -b3-  And (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A black cloud,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, S, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that has risen in any tract of the sky:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a collection of clouds rising, obstructing the horizon:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suduwdN","text_ar":"سُدُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, M, K:) [or] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sad~N","text_ar":"سَدٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sad~N","text_ar":"صَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but the former is the more approved, signify (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a cloud,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"collection of clouds, rising high, and appearing like a mountain."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M and L in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sd","text_ar":"صد"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A valley:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) so called because it becomes closed, or stopped up. (TA.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A valley containing stones and masses of rock, in which water remains for some time,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a long time:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sidadapN","text_ar":"سِدَدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, L, K:) or you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroDN bihaA sidadapN","text_ar":"اَرْضٌ بِهَا سِدَدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a land in which are valleys containing stones and masses of rock,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]; and the sing. is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sud~apN","text_ar":"سُدَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L.) ―         -b6-  And (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"departure"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"loss"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of sight:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, M:) from the same word in the first of the senses expl. in the next preceding paragraph. (M.)"}],"source_refs":["M","TA","S","A","K","AZ","L","IAar"]},{"entry_id":"n19284","headword_ar":"سِدٌّ","root":"sd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sadiydN","text_ar":"سَدِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n19396","headword_ar":"سَدٍ","root":"sdw and sdY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sadiYN","text_ar":"سَدِىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Moist;"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied in this sense to anything. (AHn, M.) ―         -b2-  And [particularly]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Moist with dew,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with night-dew,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with much thereof,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] applied to a place. (M.) And you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroDN sadiyapN","text_ar":"اَرْضٌ سَدِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A land moist with much night-dew."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layolapN sadiyapN","text_ar":"لَيْلَةٌ سَدِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A night moist with much dew:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, * TA:) the epithet ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sadK","text_ar":"سَدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is seldom applied to a day. (M, TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balaHN sadK","text_ar":"بَلَحٌ سَدٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Dates in the state in which they are termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balaH","text_ar":"بَلَح"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) accord. to As,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when they have fallen,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that have become lax in their"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vafaAriyq","text_ar":"ثَفَارِيق"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bases,"},{"kind":"text","text":"so as to be easily detached therefrom], (As, T, S, M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and moist:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, T, M:) one thereof [i. e. a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balaHap","text_ar":"بَلَحَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sadiyapN","text_ar":"سَدِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (As, T, TA:) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vuforuwq","text_ar":"ثُفْرُوق"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qimaE","text_ar":"قِمَع"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"busorap","text_ar":"بُسْرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balaHap","text_ar":"بَلَحَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) You say also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"basorN sadK","text_ar":"بَسْرٌ سَدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"busorapN sadiyapN","text_ar":"بُسْرَةٌ سَدِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is the same as ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sadaApN","text_ar":"سَدَاةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[expl. above, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sadFY","text_ar":"سَدًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","K","T","TA","As"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}